11/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- More than 1 million packs of smuggled cigarettes were seized on Tuesday (August 10th), according to an announcement by the finance ministry.
The cigarettes, bound for Bulgaria's black market, were seized at the port of Piraeus.
The ship arrived from Egypt on July 19th.
The street value of the stash is estimated at 3m euros.
An investigation is under way to determine the exact origin of the smuggled goods.
(AFP, ANA-MPA - 10/08/10)
